The paper deals with the complexity of predicting the long-term behavior of stochastic processes based on evolutions and measurements of quantum systems. This topic falls under the intersection of quantum information theory (cs.QI) and computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the simulation of quantum circuits and quantum Turing machines, which are important topics in computer science (cs.DS, cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques such as algebraic numbers, which could place it in the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
